{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":879,"text":"Today, I am going to show you"},{"time":2905,"text":"how this tablet and this virtual-reality\nheadset that I'm wearing"},{"time":7358,"text":"are going to completely\nrevolutionize science education."},{"time":12100,"text":"And I'm also going to show you"},{"time":13919,"text":"how it can make any science teacher\nmore than twice as effective."},{"time":19124,"text":"But before I show you\nhow all of this is possible,"},{"time":22612,"text":"let's talk briefly about why improving\nthe quality of science education"},{"time":28175,"text":"is so vitally important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31513,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":32698,"text":"the world is growing incredibly fast."},{"time":35322,"text":"And with that growth comes\na whole list of growing challenges,"},{"time":39231,"text":"challenges such as dealing\nwith global warming,"},{"time":42268,"text":"solving starvation and water shortages"},{"time":44655,"text":"and curing diseases,"},{"time":46131,"text":"to name just a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48402,"text":"And who, exactly, is going to help us\nsolve all of these great challenges?"},{"time":54733,"text":"Well, to a very last degree,\nit is these young students."},{"time":58194,"text":"This is the next generation\nof young, bright scientists."},{"time":62060,"text":"And in many ways, we all rely on them"},{"time":65104,"text":"for coming up with new, great innovations"},{"time":67930,"text":"to help us solve all\nthese challenges ahead of us."},{"time":72708,"text":"And so a couple of years back,"},{"time":74683,"text":"my cofounder and I were teaching\nuniversity students just like these,"},{"time":79066,"text":"only the students we were teaching\nlooked a little bit more like this here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84204,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85292,"text":"And yes, this is really\nthe reality out there"},{"time":88154,"text":"in way too many universities\naround the world:"},{"time":91703,"text":"students that are bored, disengaged"},{"time":94380,"text":"and sometimes not even sure\nwhy they're learning about a topic"},{"time":98009,"text":"in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99763,"text":"So we started looking around for new,\ninnovative teaching methods,"},{"time":104121,"text":"but what we found was quite disappointing."},{"time":106968,"text":"We saw that books were being\nturned into e-books,"},{"time":111495,"text":"blackboards were being turned\ninto YouTube videos"},{"time":114535,"text":"and lecture hall monologues\nwere being turned into MOOCs --"},{"time":117703,"text":"massive online open courses."},{"time":120694,"text":"And if you think about it,"},{"time":121965,"text":"all we're really doing here\nis taking the same content"},{"time":125572,"text":"and the same format,"},{"time":127144,"text":"and bringing it out to more students --"},{"time":130565,"text":"which is great, don't get me\nwrong, that is really great --"},{"time":133427,"text":"but the teaching method\nis still more or less the same,"},{"time":137078,"text":"no real innovation there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139863,"text":"So we started looking elsewhere."},{"time":141906,"text":"What we found was that flight simulators\nhad been proven over and over again"},{"time":146557,"text":"to be far more effective"},{"time":148048,"text":"when used in combination with real,\nin-flight training to train the pilots."},{"time":153338,"text":"And so we thought to ourselves:"},{"time":155532,"text":"Why not just apply that to science?"},{"time":157893,"text":"Why not build a virtual\nlaboratory simulator?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":163563,"text":"Well, we did it."},{"time":164835,"text":"We basically set out to create"},{"time":166677,"text":"a fully simulated, one-to-one,\nvirtual reality laboratory simulator,"},{"time":172316,"text":"where the students\ncould perform experiments"},{"time":174537,"text":"with mathematical equations"},{"time":176471,"text":"that would simulate what would\nhappen in a real-world lab."},{"time":179714,"text":"But not just simple simulations --"},{"time":181417,"text":"we would also create advanced simulations"},{"time":183507,"text":"with top universities like MIT,"},{"time":185455,"text":"to bring out cutting-edge cancer\nresearch to these students."},{"time":190520,"text":"And suddenly, the universities\ncould save millions of dollars"},{"time":193427,"text":"by letting the students\nperform virtual experiments"},{"time":196381,"text":"before they go into the real laboratory."},{"time":200303,"text":"And not only that; now,\nthey could also understand --"},{"time":202859,"text":"even on a molecular level\ninside the machine --"},{"time":205316,"text":"what is happening to the machines."},{"time":208016,"text":"And then they could suddenly perform"},{"time":209939,"text":"dangerous experiments in the labs as well."},{"time":212591,"text":"For instance also here,"},{"time":214101,"text":"learning about salmonella bacteria,\nwhich is an important topic"},{"time":217737,"text":"that many schools cannot teach\nfor good safety reasons."},{"time":222315,"text":"And we, of course, quiz the students"},{"time":224076,"text":"and then give the teachers\na full dashboard,"},{"time":226505,"text":"so they fully understand\nwhere the students are at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230134,"text":"But we didn't stop there,"},{"time":231366,"text":"because we had seen just\nhow important meaning is"},{"time":233715,"text":"for the students' engagement in the class."},{"time":236025,"text":"So we brought in game designers"},{"time":237771,"text":"to create fun and engaging stories."},{"time":240676,"text":"For instance, here in this case,"},{"time":242534,"text":"where the students have to solve\na mysterious CSI murder case"},{"time":246681,"text":"using their core science skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251861,"text":"And the feedback we got\nwhen we launched all of this"},{"time":254329,"text":"was quite overwhelmingly positive."},{"time":256305,"text":"Here we have 300 students,"},{"time":258132,"text":"all passionately solving CSI murder cases"},{"time":260871,"text":"while learning core science skills."},{"time":262760,"text":"And what I love the most about this"},{"time":265029,"text":"is really when the students\ncome up to me sometimes afterwards,"},{"time":268697,"text":"all surprised and a little confused,"},{"time":270836,"text":"and say, \"I just spent two hours\nin this virtual lab,"},{"time":276432,"text":"and ... and I didn't check Facebook.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":278635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":279988,"text":"That's how engaging and immersive\nthis really is for the students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284663,"text":"And so, to investigate\nwhether this really worked,"},{"time":287507,"text":"a learning psychologist\ndid a study with 160 students --"},{"time":291934,"text":"that was from Stanford University\nand Technical University of Denmark."},{"time":296204,"text":"And what they did is split\nthe students into two groups."},{"time":299760,"text":"One group would only use\nthe virtual laboratory simulations,"},{"time":304035,"text":"the other group would only use\ntraditional teaching methods,"},{"time":307759,"text":"and they had the same amount of time."},{"time":310801,"text":"Then, interestingly,"},{"time":311977,"text":"they gave the students a test\nbefore and after the experiment,"},{"time":315668,"text":"so they could clearly measure\nthe learning impact of the students."},{"time":320045,"text":"And what they found"},{"time":321237,"text":"was a surprisingly high 76 percent\nincrease in the learning effectiveness"},{"time":327062,"text":"when using virtual laboratories\nover traditional teaching methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332349,"text":"But even more interestingly,"},{"time":333858,"text":"the second part of this study investigated"},{"time":337096,"text":"what the teacher's impact\nwas on the learning."},{"time":340024,"text":"And what they found"},{"time":341199,"text":"was that when you combined\nthe virtual laboratories"},{"time":343885,"text":"with teacher-led coaching and mentoring,"},{"time":346513,"text":"then we saw a total 101 percent\nincrease in the learning effectiveness,"},{"time":352353,"text":"which effectively doubles\nthe science teacher's impact"},{"time":356809,"text":"with the same amount of time spent."},{"time":361784,"text":"So a couple of months back,"},{"time":364518,"text":"we started asking ourselves --"},{"time":366055,"text":"we have a wonderful team now\nof learning psychologists"},{"time":368626,"text":"and teachers and scientists\nand game developers --"},{"time":371006,"text":"and we started asking ourselves:"},{"time":372571,"text":"How can we keep ourselves to our promise"},{"time":375190,"text":"of constantly reimagining education?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378178,"text":"And today, I am really excited\nto be presenting what we came up with"},{"time":383303,"text":"and have been working\nincredibly hard to create."},{"time":388228,"text":"I will explain briefly what this is."},{"time":390885,"text":"Basically, I take my mobile phone --"},{"time":393645,"text":"most students already\nhave these, smartphones --"},{"time":396375,"text":"and I plug it into this virtual-reality\nheadset, a low-cost headset."},{"time":400923,"text":"And now what I can effectively do is,"},{"time":402916,"text":"I can literally step\ninto this virtual world."},{"time":406090,"text":"We'll have some of you\nin the audience also get to try this,"},{"time":409198,"text":"because it is really something\nthat you have to try"},{"time":412378,"text":"to fully feel how immersive it really is."},{"time":414697,"text":"It literally feels like I just stepped\ninside this virtual lab."},{"time":418498,"text":"Do you see me up on the screen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420025,"text":"Audience: Yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421200,"text":"Michael Bodekaer: Great! Awesome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422827,"text":"So basically, I have just\nturned my mobile phone"},{"time":425749,"text":"into a fully simulated, million-dollar\nIvy League laboratory"},{"time":429437,"text":"with all this amazing equipment\nthat I can interact with."},{"time":432286,"text":"I can, for instance, pick up the pipette\nand do experiments with it."},{"time":435683,"text":"I have my E-Ggel, my PCR\nand -- oh, look there,"},{"time":438127,"text":"I have my next-generation\nsequencing machine,"},{"time":440672,"text":"and there I even have\nmy electron microscope."},{"time":444194,"text":"I mean, who's carrying around\nan electron microscope in their pocket?"},{"time":447648,"text":"And here I have my machine,"},{"time":449544,"text":"I can do different experiments\non the machine."},{"time":451738,"text":"And over here I have the door,"},{"time":453216,"text":"I can go into other experiments,"},{"time":455608,"text":"I can perform in the laboratories."},{"time":457565,"text":"And here, I have my learning tablet."},{"time":459795,"text":"This is an intelligent tablet"},{"time":461273,"text":"that allows me to read\nabout relevant theory."},{"time":464145,"text":"As you can see, I can interact with it."},{"time":466471,"text":"I can watch videos and see\ncontent that is relevant"},{"time":470389,"text":"to the experiment\nthat I'm performing right now."},{"time":474074,"text":"Then over here, I have Marie."},{"time":475501,"text":"She is my teacher --\nmy lab assistant --"},{"time":479044,"text":"and what she does is guides me\nthrough this whole laboratory."},{"time":482245,"text":"And very soon,"},{"time":483428,"text":"the teachers will be able\nto literally teleport themselves"},{"time":486420,"text":"into this virtual world\nthat I'm in right now"},{"time":489003,"text":"and help me, guide me,\nthrough this whole experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492257,"text":"And now before I finalize this,"},{"time":494591,"text":"I want to show you\nan even cooler thing, I think --"},{"time":497583,"text":"something you cannot\neven do in real laboratories."},{"time":500643,"text":"This is a PCR machine."},{"time":501905,"text":"I'm now going to start this experiment."},{"time":504409,"text":"And what I just did is literally\nshrunk myself a million times"},{"time":508666,"text":"into the size of a molecule --"},{"time":510249,"text":"and it really feels like it,\nyou have to try this."},{"time":512622,"text":"So now it feels like\nI'm standing inside the machine"},{"time":515249,"text":"and I'm seeing all the DNA,\nand I see the molecules."},{"time":517866,"text":"I see the polymerase\nand the enzymes and so forth."},{"time":521493,"text":"And I can see how in this case,"},{"time":523120,"text":"DNA is being replicated millions of times,"},{"time":526221,"text":"just like it's happening\ninside your body right now."},{"time":529078,"text":"And I can really feel and understand\nhow all of this works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534219,"text":"Now, I hope that gives you\na little bit of a sense"},{"time":537537,"text":"of the possibilities\nin these new teaching methods."},{"time":544230,"text":"And I want to also emphasize"},{"time":545596,"text":"that everything you just saw\nalso works on iPads and laptops"},{"time":549311,"text":"without the headsets."},{"time":550506,"text":"I say that for a very important reason."},{"time":553394,"text":"In order for us to really\nempower and inspire"},{"time":556903,"text":"the next generation of scientists,"},{"time":559095,"text":"we really need teachers\nto drive the adoption"},{"time":562643,"text":"of new technologies in the classroom."},{"time":566542,"text":"And so in many ways,"},{"time":568444,"text":"I believe that the next big,\nquantum leap in science education"},{"time":572823,"text":"lies no longer with the technology,"},{"time":575156,"text":"but rather with the teachers' decision"},{"time":577061,"text":"to push forward and adopt\nthese technologies"},{"time":580290,"text":"inside the classrooms."},{"time":582061,"text":"And so it is our hope that more\nuniversities and schools and teachers"},{"time":585922,"text":"will collaborate with technology companies"},{"time":588811,"text":"to realize this full potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592989,"text":"And so,"},{"time":594458,"text":"lastly, I'd like to leave you\nwith a little story"},{"time":597315,"text":"that really inspires me."},{"time":598901,"text":"And that is the story of Jack Andraka."},{"time":601346,"text":"Some of you might already know him."},{"time":603132,"text":"Jack invented a new, groundbreaking\nlow-cost test for pancreatic cancer"},{"time":610148,"text":"at the age 15."},{"time":613758,"text":"And when Jack shares his story\nof how he did this huge breakthrough,"},{"time":617521,"text":"he also explains that one thing\nalmost prevented him"},{"time":621370,"text":"from making this breakthrough."},{"time":623543,"text":"And that was that he did not\nhave access to real laboratories,"},{"time":628627,"text":"because he was too inexperienced"},{"time":631180,"text":"to be allowed in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633853,"text":"Now, imagine if we could bring"},{"time":636079,"text":"Ivy League, million-dollar\nvirtual laboratories"},{"time":639372,"text":"out to all these students just like Jack,"},{"time":641467,"text":"all over the world,"},{"time":643098,"text":"and give them the latest, greatest,\nmost fancy machines you can imagine"},{"time":646678,"text":"that would quite literally\nmake any scientist in here"},{"time":649248,"text":"jump up and down out of pure excitement."},{"time":651745,"text":"And then imagine how that\nwould empower and inspire"},{"time":656379,"text":"a whole new generation\nof young and bright scientists,"},{"time":660582,"text":"ready to innovate and change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664187,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665362,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}